VR for PC
Creation date start 11/28/20 finish 12/6/20 Made by Zachary wise for college project.
Consoles are in a unique place for virtual reality, although it is at a lower overall quality than the pc counterpart the general price is cheaper as well. Due to the lower output the game library is smaller and its capabilities are in a similar situation.
With both major consoles being harder to mod, the games remain simple, larger games wouldn’t work and only a few vr systems are compatible with consoles. Sony has a vr just for their PlayStation which is a cheap option for beginners and their console has a decent variety of games
Virtual reality for console is strictly games with a small side of watching shows, nothing else due to advancements happening slower, however the next generation of consoles has just arrived and with it brings larger hardware, currently there are no special vr games but in the future creators can make games that are closer to what can be run on pc.
Although the console has a smaller library and less powerful hardware then its pc counterpart it remains the cheaper and simpler option, with easier set ups and easy controls this is a wonderful option for the skeptical players or for simply those on a budget.
A viewing library for console slowing you to view a documentary on each biome/location.
